column3: Edge of main beaver pond, so up to 5 in places - averaged to 4.  Open water 40%.
Crataegus monogyna, Sambucus nigra, P. x canadensis
Previously arable, south east corner near fence
possibly var microcarpa, or possible hybrid, had similarities with R.crispus leaves but only the smallest teeth on fruit wings.
Range 2-4 as near a beaver canal
Salix cinerea.  There is a dead tree (Hybrid Poplar or Bat Willow), felled by Beavers across sample point.
Salix alba var. caerulea, Salix cinerea
Open water 100. This was on edge of original drainage channel, near a clump of Iris and overhanging Hazel with Hop - now much more open due to beaver felling and damming into large pond.
Range 2-5, edge of main beaver lodge
Fraxinus excelsior, Tilia sp., Salix alba var.caerulea
Corylus avellana, Quercus sp., Fraxinus excelsior
not quite far enough east due to beaver canals
Range 1-5 next to a beaver canal
Salix alba var. caerulea high canopy
Quercus sp., Acer campestre, Tilia sp.
Tilia sp., Acer campestre, Fagus sylvatica
small tree forming canopy in mid storey layer
Acer campestre, Ulmus procera agg. Near to hedge and fence
